	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Like nesasm, there is nothing significantly wrong with nbasic.  Most of it is just doing a find/replace with asm.  Just because the people who used it didn't understand the NES doesn't mean the tools are bad.  
<br />
<br />Without some form of cheap rewritable storage media I don't see how this computer will be too useful.  With out a floppy or cassette it is harder (aka more expensive) to store documents, write new programs, or distribute programs.  Sure it has a cart slot but thats not useful for starving marvin to send a program he wrote to his friend.
<br />
<br />I was much more impressed when the story was it being an apple 2  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />

		

